# Next.js Architecture

- Reuse existing components, hooks, utilities, and services (DRY).
- Keep files focused and under 200 lines where practical.
- Shared UI → `components/ui`, shared app UI → `components/common`, features → `components/<feature>`.
- Hooks → `hooks/`, utilities → `lib/`, constants → `lib/constants/`, types → `types/`, server actions → `actions/`, API calls → `services/`.

Before writing code, check: does similar code exist? Can an existing hook/service be extended?
